RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 96. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EASTBOUND bobbled leaving the gate then took back shortly after, raced outside a rival at the back early, looked to advance on the far turn back lacked room behind a pair of rivals, angled widest at the top of the stretch, rallied under hand urging and proved best in the end. BALTHAZAR settled inside, tipped two wide leaving the far turn, moved out further and bumped rival entering the stretch, rallied three deed and took over midstretch, showed the way into the final sixteenth but was overtaken by the winner late. QUALITY WINS broke a step slow, went up outside the top pair early then dropped back off the leaders while racing a bit green on the clubhouse turn and backstretch, rounded the far turn three wide, got bumped by inner rival entering the stretch, bid four deep between foes in the final furlong and finished a game third. NASHOBA'S JOY pulled on the inside around the clubhouse turn and early on the backstretch, continued to save ground at the back through the far turn, moved out in the final furlong and summoned a mild rally. CLASSICALLY stumbled to the front, vied inside a pair into the first turn then ceded command, bid two wide around the far turn and took over late on the bend, lost command in upper stretch and flattened in the late stages. DURAN was off a bit slow to start then went up and started to pull between rivals then tugged clear, challenged around the far turn from outside, relinquished the lead past the quarter pole, fought back to regain the lead outside the eighth pole then weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAMPLIGHTER JACK broke in and bumped rival, sprinted clear and moved inside, controlled the pace up with a comfortable lead up the backstretch, held a diminished lead while cutting the corner into the stretch, then responded to a few taps of right-handed encouragement by drawing away in deep stretch. LOVESICK BLUES tracked from inside, angled out on the far turn and took aim three wide outside a rival into the stretch, chased the winner through the lane but had to settle for second best. WEEGEE got sandwiched leaving the gate, raced in mid-pack outside a rival, rounded the far turn three then four wide and rallied to beat KEENEBEC for the show honors. KENNEBEC bumped with WEEGEE at the start, raced in mid-pack on the inside, hugged the rail into the drive and gained the show. OVERDUE was bothered from inside at the start, raced on the inside near the back into the clubhouse turn, got boxed in on the far turn, angled out into the stretch and improved position. DOMINANT SOUL was closest in pursuit while moving to the inside, cut into the lead on the far turn, took aim two wide into the stretch but weakened in the final furlong. MOODY JIM (IRE) broke a step slow and unhurried on the inside in the opening stages, went two to three wide on the far turn, steered out in the drive and failed to menace. SHOTGUN EXPRESS (IRE) had his shadow roll come loose in the beginning and bounced throughout the race, saved ground off the pace and failed to menace. BIG BUZZ traveled two wide near the back early, rounded the far turn four wide, moved out in the drive and was never a factor.
